<docs>
   <doc for="SplitterDesigner">
 <summary>
 <para>Provides design-time functionality for the <see cref='System.Windows.Forms.Splitter'/> control.</para>
 </summary>
 <remarks>
 <para><see cref='System.Windows.Forms.Design.SplitterDesigner'/> draws a visible border on the splitter if it doesn't have a border so 
    the user knows where the boundaries of the splitter lie.</para>
 </remarks>
   </doc>
   <doc for="SplitterDesigner.NonBrowsableEventNames">
 <summary>
    <para>Gets or sets a string containing a list of non-browsable event 
       names.</para>
 </summary>
   </doc>
   <doc for="SplitterDesigner.DrawBorder">
 <summary>
      This draws a nice border around our panel.  We need
      this because the panel can have no border and you can't
      tell where it is.
 </summary>
   </doc>
   <doc for="SplitterDesigner.OnPaintAdornments">
 <summary>
    <para>Handles the PaintAdornments event. 
       Overrides the base class method.</para>
 </summary>
 <remarks>
    <para>This method checks to determine if there is no border on the panel. If there is not, this draws 
       one so that the panel shape is visible at design-time.</para>
 </remarks>
   </doc>
   <doc for="SplitterDesigner.WndProc">
 <summary>
    <para>Provides processing for Windows messages.</para>
 </summary>
   </doc>
</docs>

